The immediate past governor of Delta State, Dr. Emmanuel Ewetan Uduaghan has dumped the All Progressives Congress (APC) for the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Uduaghan, who dumped the PDP in 2018 announced his return on Monday. The Delta South Senate aspirant in 2019 had said his desire to attract development and bring a permanent solution to the Niger Delta crisis drew him to the APC. However, on Monday, Uduaghan in a post on his Facebook page said he returned to PDP to join forces with the largest party. “I am back to join forces with other party greats to strengthen our party, the largest Party in Africa -PDP! “Having tasted the other side, it feels refreshing to be back home! “Thank you all for receiving me back. It feels like I never left.”